name: Aztec restoration #8.5
description: Hand embroidered detail from plate 9 of the 16th century sacred aztec manuscript the Codex Borgia. This depicts Xochiquetzal, the goddess of fertility, sexuality, pregnancy and traditional female handicrafts. She is seated on a throne upon a jaguar skin, wearing an eagle headdress, colourful patterned clothing and an elaborate turquoise nose piercing or "xiuhyacamitl".
